      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PROUD MISS (10) has been around the mark this distance range and will find this more suitable than Ipswich and the Gold Coast, her last two. Has a handy 2kg claim today and may settle more forward. This isn't hard, and she gets her chance on a quick backup. OAKFIELD GALAXY (3) raced over a mile at Ipswich on the same day and wasn't too far away. His Gold Coast placing three back over 1800m reads well, and he also has winning claims. LUCKY JOKER (2) came from the back in the same race and finished a length ahead of the above. He also deserves plenty of consideration over longer. HABERFIELD (7) presents third-up off two sprint placings. Came from a long way back at Dalby last time and deserves a chance over this longer trip. Has the rail and a handy 2kg claim. PELLINOR (5) may be the best of the rest.",
